        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 18 at 8:13PM CDT by NWS Memphis TN</headline>
        <description>At 813 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Fair Oaks, or 10 miles southwest of Wynne, moving northeast at 25
mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Wynne, Hydrick, Rosenbaum, Fitzgerald Crossing, Crow Creek,
Wittsburg, Village Creek State Park, Fair Oaks, Brushy Lake, McElroy,
Vanndale, Colt, Kinton, Fair Field, Ellis Chapel, Levesque, Hamlin,
L'angville, and Caldwell.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
